<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/13 (Thu.) How AI can save our humanity/ How to build (and rebuild) trust (Host: Cammy)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=234&amp;p=248#p248"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">[Session I: How AI can save our humanity (Kai-Fu Lee | TED2018)</span><br /><a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/kai_fu_lee_how_ai_can_save_our_humanity?utm_source=tedcomshare&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=tedspread" class="postlink">https://www.ted.com/talks/kai_fu_lee_how_ai_can_save_our_humanity?utm_source=tedcomshare&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=tedspread</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion Questions:</span><br />1. What kind of jobs will be replaced by AI in near future? What jobs will still be around in 20 years? Please share your thoughts. <br />2. From this speech, we learned “How AI and mankind can coexist”. Please share 3 points of your learning or thoughts with your team members.<br />3. What do you think that people will regret most about your life when your time is up? Failing to fulfill your duty and obligations? Or failing to follow your dreams? Please share some stories or your comments at your table.<br />4.  How do you arrange your work-life balance? Please share your experiences or suggestions with your team members.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II: How to build (and rebuild) trust (TED2018 Frances Frei)</span><br /><a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/frances_frei_how_to_build_and_rebuild_trust/transcript" class="postlink">https://www.ted.com/talks/frances_frei_how_to_build_and_rebuild_trust/transcript</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion Questions:</span><br />1. Had you ever experienced “trust is broken” in your past life? Please share your stories or the stories you learned at your table.<br />2. In this video, it mentioned “And if you do nothing else, please put away your cell phone.” It is the largest distraction magnet yet to be made, and it is super difficult to create empathy and trust in its presence.” Do you agree it or not? Why?<br />3. Please share” 4 Ways to Communicate Effectively “with your table members.<br />4. If trust is broken in a relationship, can it be repaired? How to rebuild trust? Please share your comments from this video with your table members.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Thu Dec 06, 2018 11:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
